examples.en: 'How was I to know!' Jenny raged.
The manager raged at the umpire.
The passion for play raged in him without measure.
He raged at us for forgetting to order a replacement.
Those northern nations raged over all these parts of the world.
She raged about the injustice of their decision.
He was sorry he had raged at her earlier.
A fierce debate raged over which artist's work should be chosen for the prize.
